review_blob: Mostly clear golden orange pour with a small head that fades to a thin ring. Aroma is fairly dank and pretty awesome. Big citrus and pineapple, moderate pine, and light peach. Tastes slightly sweet up front with a moderate bitter finish. Great mix of tropical fruit, citrus, and pine. Great crackery malt base. So easy to drink
beer_name: Evil Twin / 7venth Sun Citra Sunshine Slacker

review_blob: Lots of foam when pouring. Aroma has bretta tones, grapefruit and soapy tones. Flavour has grapefruit, bretta tones and some citrus. Flavour was quite straightforward and easy compared to the taste

ours a cloudy medium orange with a loose and fizzy whitish head that goes away. Mild mango and apricot nose. Creamy medium body with bright lively carbonation. Mango and apricots on the mid palate. Refreshing and light, but very subdued in the flavors and aromatics.
Shocked over this one aroma of cherries was present when opened, dark brown color, no head, taste just like cherry cola i was shocked alcohol lingers at the end a decent beer

Pours clear dark gold with a medium, frothy white head, medium retention with good lacing. Aroma is guava, mango, honey malt. Flavor is honey malt, earthy and nutty with guava notes, papaya and light bitterness with a dry finish. Light body and medium carbonation.

Pours a clear orangish amber with an off-white head that dissipates to the edges. Aroma has a nice gingerbread note to it with a decent amount of molasses and bread underlying. Flavor is a bit more subdued with a nice gingerbread note backed by molasses and some sweet grains.
Pours a deep black with a brown head. Bourbon, vanilla, oak, chocolate aromas. Flavors of bourbon and chocolate, with some alcohol/burn on the finish. great great imp stout

God god this was1 awesome beer Pours black with an attractive light brown head and a chocolate and chili pepper aroma. There is a full-bodied dark molasses flavor with lots of cocoa and a mildly spicy finish. It all goes together very nicely.
beer_name: Evil Twin An Ms Chili Jess

review_blob: clear and bright golden colour under a solid and long lasting white foam; some oily grassy hops hit the nose; the oily feeling persists on the tongue in top of a medium malt backbone, sweet and with no bitterness to mention; grassy finish

on tap poured a clear yellow with a lasting creamy white head. Aromas of straw, earthiness, lemon zest and grapefruit zest. Palate was light to medium bodied and smooth with a dry finish. Flavors of straw, pine, grapefruit and light lemon zest with a smooth dry lingering bitter finish.
on tap Mint chocolate chip aroma. Dark brown pour with a mocha head. Mint, milk chocolate, and bitter toasted malt notes. Impressive. Doesnt drink like a 10%er. Above average body and mouth feel.

on tap Golden color, small white head. Aroma is fruity, wooden, floral and mildly spicy. Flavor is fruity, herbal, floral, malty and toffeeish with some slight honey like notes. Pleasantly balanced and hides the ABV well.
on tap Hazy amber color with medium white head. Caramel malt, citrus hops in aroma. Tart taste with strong citrus hops with lemon, grapefruit, zest, pines. Long tart hoppy bitter finish. Tasty.

Pours dep brown into a snifter. Mocha head with medium retention recedes to mottle surface. Sweet pit fruit and pine aromas. Creamy dark caramel and oak upfront turning to smores before the lasting charred pepper skin finish

Cloudy yellow pour with a small fizzy head and fades to a thick ring. Aromas are sour lemons, wheat, and flowers. Tastes moderately sour. Grainy wheat, lots of lemons, a touch of flowers in the finish.

Pours black with low tan head. Aroma of vanilla, chocolate, bourbon AND rum, figs and raisins. Yum. Taste is big boozy with dark chocolate and coffee followed by a milk chocolate sweetness in the finish. Rich, creamy body with soft carbonation
beer_name: Omnipollo Noa Pecan Mud Cake - Bourbon

review_blob: on tap holy crap this was awesome Dark brown with a beige head. Full body with low carbonation. Nice bitterness with subtle sweetness. Peat, roasted malts, whiskey, caramel, dark chocolate, coffee and spices. Tasty strong brew.
Clear amber with off-white head. Aromas of big malt, slight dark fruit. Tastes of malt, corn, wheat, light citrus. Light body with a dry finish

Hazy, ruby-amber colored, some floaties visible, stable off-White foamy layer; dried red berries, caramel and delicate traces of Wood and vanilla in the dark-malty nose; moderate sweet and mildly bitter flavor, medium bodied, not very soft; lingering vinous-fruity and caramelly finish with a slight bitterness in the aftertaste.
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #6 - Seven Kingdoms

review_blob: Reddish amber and clear appearance with a white head. Mild aroma of caramel, toffee, light chocolate and toasted grains. Similar flavor, nutty malty sweetness and light earthy hop bitterness nothing special going on here

Pours a clear gold with a thin white head. Earthy musk and a hint of dry brett on the nose, a touch of orange and lemond candy. medium bodied, sweet musk and a bit of spicy brett. Dries out nicely, clean and earthy. Finishes up with lingering black pepper, yeast, crackers, slow grapefruit. Lots of subtlety here, well balanced and easy drinking.
on tap Color is hazy orange with small white head. Aromas and flavours: Fruits, citrus, grape, caramel and hops. Very fresh and enjoyable
beer_name: Zipline Gin Barrel Aged Rye IPA

review_blob: golden with small head. i thought i would like this the best of the three varieties, and was saving it for last, but its rather underwhelming and definitely in third place. average cider with light bourbon. thin.

ours a dark, hazy brown color with a small tan head. Aroma of smoked meats and hickory, earth, chocolate, roast, and toast. Flavor of smoked hickory and pork, chocolate, coffee, and earth. Medium-bodied, with moderate carbonation and a mellow smoky mouthfeel. Not a whole lot to say about this one except that it is such a well-done smoked beer

dark amber pour with a thick head that fades to a cap. aroma is rye bread, caramel and light woody hop Initial light body rolls into toffee and bready sweetness. peppery rye, light floral/woody hop finish with lingering spice
hazy gold, thinnest oily white ring. Skunky nose is tangerine, meaty and earthy. Salty flavor has meat, dry tangerine, spritzy carbonation and light profile with long lasting citric bite

Wheaty grainy nose with noble hop notes. Medium amber clear with thin off-white lacing head. Medium body with medium-high carbonation. Starts medium dry with wheat and pale malt sweetness. Noble hop bite, carbonic acidity, and light hop finish
From tap. Pours hazy yellow with a small white head. Aroma is acetic, light fruity. Citric, fruity and mild peachy. Lingering citric and smooth fruit
Nice glowing amber body with medium head. Nose is hoppy, fruity, floral. Taste is nice hoppy with some honey notes. Pretty good stuff. Lots of pineapple in there, but nice and subtle. Enjoyable.

Pours a hazy golden yellow from the bottle with fluffy white head that dissipates to leave moderate lace. Aroma of sweet fruity notes, definitely passion fruity. Taste follows, clean and simple, on the fruit for sure.
Black with a brown head. Roasty aroma full of coffee beans and some cocoa. Bittersweet flavor, roasty, full of coffee, with some dark chocolate. Full-bodied.
tap; pours clear golden with a white head. Aroma is tropical fruit, grapefruit, and the like. Taste is not very bitter. Very citrusy. Not very bitter. Kind of juicy. Light and mellow IPA.
beer_name: Firestone Walker Luponic Distortion Revolution No. 001

review_blob: Pours bright orange Amber color with faint tiny bits floating around. Smells bright citrus orange zest some bitterness. Taste is bitter citrus and malty. Straight forward and pretty drinkable
Pours hazy golden yellow with white head. Aroma is lemon, grain, wheat, and some banana. Flavor is wheat, banana, clove, lemon, and some light grain. Mouthfeel and carbonation were decent
Poured golden with a small cream colored head. Light grassy aroma. Light honey flavor with some fruitiness and hops. Mildly bitter finish. Good.

Golden color, white head. Sort of a blend of west coast and east coast hoppiness, leaning a little more toward the west. Very piney. Balanced with sweet malt. Would like it to be more intense in flavor

Clear golden orange with a finger of off-white head. Aromas of watermelon bubble gum, flowery notes, light floral and citrus. Tastes of watermelon candy and Kool Aid, citrus, floral notes. Medium body with a semi-dry finish. Alcohol is super well masked
beer_name: Ballast Point Dorado Double IPA - Watermelon

beer_brewer_name: Coney Island Brewing Company (Boston Beer Company)
review_blob: Ginger smelled when opened not to overpowering, pours a off color gold taste of ginger is very prominent no aftertaste a decent effort

Not bad took ne back to the day of sitting on the porch with grandpa smells of ginger was present when opened poured a clear gold color taste of ginger with slight alcohol no lingering aftertaste I liked it
beer_name: Small Town Not Your Fathers Ginger Ale

review_blob: On tap holy cow this was awesome Cloudy dark brown color, large brown head with good retention. Aroma of funky dark fruit, prunes, raisins. Taste is softly sour summer fruit, dates, sour cherries

Pours clear, deep amber with off-white head. Aroma is toasted and caramel malts, orange peel, citrus and floral notes, and faint dank. Flavor is hop forward with solid citrus bitterness that melds nicely with the caramel and tangerine flavors; very tasty

on tap Good coloring. Not sweet at all. A definite spike in the bittering, doughy, peaty, quick crisp finish, although some tannic qualities linger on. Not ale-y enough, but well-balanced and very drinkable., I expected it to get a little bit more caramel as it warmed, but it didnt. This almost reminds me of an alt. Good, drinkable, but just mildly Scottish.

on tap at the casino Served a dark brown with a thick head and nice lacing. Aroma of roasted malt, dark chocolate, nutty, with coffee and a bit earthy. taste of roasted malt, dark chocolate, touch of coffee and nuts. Mild bitterness and a clean finish. A good medium body, smooth and creamy feel.

Pours a hazy amber color with a large two finger thick off white head. Light lacing. Aroma is oak, vanilla, esters, and light spice. Very nice. Its not strong, but nice and mellow. Flavor is full of oak, spice, esters, light citrus, light vanilla and toasted malt. Not a lot of hops, but the oak really shines. Smooth finish. Medium to full body

Small tan head that mostly diminished, fine-small sized bubbles, fair lacing, uncarbonated, transparent, and an orange brown hue. Sweet, fruity, port and alcohol aroma. Flavor was malty, vinuous, fruity and some hops. Medium body. very nicely done
beer_name: Against the Grain This Is Not A Beer

review_blob: Pours bright clear orange with two finger pillowy head. smell is quite the powerful punch of vibrant citrus and pine with a dark resinous tone. Danklike qualities. Taste is more heavy pine, resin, some grapefruit and more dank. Sweet caramel undertones. Almost a creaminess to the finish with a slick mouthfeel. Very nice
beer_name: Oskar Blues Deviant Dales India Pale Ale

review_blob: The aroma consists of chocolate, caramel, coffee, and a touch of vanilla. It pours a dark brown, virtually black, with no transparency and a small brown head. The flavor starts with dark chocolate and a touch of vanilla. The finish has moderate coffee with a hint of black licorice. Its full bodied with mild carbonation.

on tap Pours clear, dark gold with a robust, white foam head. Toasty malt nsoe with touches of caramel, some lightly tangy citrus. Medium sweet flavor with moderate bitterness, orange and lemon citrus, faint alcohol, grapefruit, some lightly toasted grass. Medium bodied with average carbonation. Moderately resinous to finish, some pine and grass, a bit of toasty sugar, dry citrus.

another tribute to Iron Maiden Pours a clear amber golden color, topped with a medium small white head, quickly settling. Fruity nose, some candy presence and grassy hops. Sweet feel on the nose. Taste is sweet, not too much, mildly malty with moderately mild bitterness. Sharp finish, slightly alcohol burn, but very short
Dark brown pour with a thick off-white head. Aromas of toasted nuts and chocolate. Taste is chewy, dark chocolate, light spice. Sweet, light tarry oiliness. Earthy too. Interesting.
